   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Go to <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>App Launcher </uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol> Admin</uicontrol>
               </menucascade>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>New.</uicontrol>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Name </uicontrol>field, input APTS_DoNotCopyOpportunityToAdobeAgreement.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Set the <uicontrol>Value</uicontrol> to "true". </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_zpq_b2k_rcc">
                  <image height="195"
                         placement="break"
                         width="1159"
                         href="../attachments/163938942/163940374.png"
                         id="image_aqq_b2k_rcc"/>
               </fig>
               <p>Power-Adobe Custom Settings contains a <uicontrol>Don't Copy
                     Opportunity</uicontrol> flag that allows you to prevent the Opportunity field
                  from being copied to the Adobe Agreement object. This can be set as a default for
                  the organization, or for individual Profile and User levels. </p>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
